    <briefdescription>
<para>Configurable assertion macro for SyntropicOS. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="syn__assert_8h_1ad36711aab4d7fb37f59998aa445c036e" kindref="member">SYN_ASSERT(expr)</ref> evaluates <computeroutput>expr</computeroutput> and, if false, calls <ref refid="syn__assert_8h_1ac1b7fa5fbbd92a9a6b5793bac6263db1" kindref="member">syn_assert_failed()</ref> with the file name and line number. The user can override <ref refid="syn__assert_8h_1ac1b7fa5fbbd92a9a6b5793bac6263db1" kindref="member">syn_assert_failed()</ref> to implement custom behavior (e.g., log to UART, blink an LED, enter debugger).</para>
<para>Define SYN_DISABLE_ASSERT before including this header (or in syn_config.h) to compile out all assertions for release builds. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
